Citation.sTitle: Excess Molar Enthalpies of p-Cymene + r-Pinene + a-Pinene at (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K and at Atmospheric Pressure
Citation.sAbstract: Excess molar enthalpies (Hm,123 E ), measured at (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K in a Calvet low-temperature microcalorimeter, are reported for the ternary mixture of p-cymene (1)+R-pinene (2) + a-pinene (3) at atmospheric pressure. The results serve to show that all the experimental Hm,123 E values are positive and that they increase with an increase in temperature. In all cases, maximum values were observed in the vicinity of x1=0.5. Furthermore, at constant x1, the measured Hm,123 E values increase as the ratio of x2/x3 increases.
